diff:1347124820:1347124820:=1,48d0%0a%3c %25width=100pct%25Attach:ItalianDinnerParty.png%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#ingredients]]%0a%3c !!Ingredients%0a%3c * &frac12; ounce dried porcini mushrooms%0a%3c * &frac12; pound shiitake mushrooms%0a%3c * 1 bay leaf%0a%3c * 1 cinnamon stick, broken in half%0a%3c * 3 black peppercorns%0a%3c * kosher salt%0a%3c * 1 pound mixed mushroom (such as oyster and cremini)%0a%3c * 6 tablespoons unsalted butter%0a%3c * 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil%0a%3c * 1 clove garlic, finely chopped%0a%3c * &frac14; teaspoon red pepper flakes%0a%3c * 8 ounces butternut squash, peeled, seeded, and diced%0a%3c * 2 cups arborio rice%0a%3c * 1 cup dry white wine%0a%3c * &frac12; cup grated aged gouda or parmesan cheese, plus shaved cheese for garnish%0a%3c * &frac12; cup chopped fresh parsley%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#directions]]%0a%3c !!Directions%0a%3c %0a%3c # Soak porcinis in 5 cups hot water for 30 minutes. Strain into saucepan, squeezing the liquid from the procinis. Chop the porcinis and set aside.%0a%3c %0a%3c # Make the mushroom broth: Remove the shiitake stems and transfer to a separate saucepan. Add 5 cups water, the bay leaf, &frac12; cinnamon stick, peppercorns and %25frac12; teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil, cook 3 minutes, then remove from heat and set aside to infuse, 30 minutes. Strain into the saucepan with the porcini soaking liquid, squeezing the liquid from the shiitake stems; discard the solids.%0a%3c %0a%3c # Meanwhile, chop the shiitake mushroom caps and mixed mushrooms. Heat 3 tablespoons butter and 1 tablespoon olive oil in an extra-large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the garlic, red pepper flakes and the remaining &frac12; cinnamon stick and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Add the shiitake caps and the mixed mushrooms in an even layer and cook, undisturbed, until browned, about 5 minutes. Stir and continue cooking until the mushrooms are soft, about 3 more minutes. Season with salt and discard the cinnamon stick.%0a%3c %0a%3c # Bring the mushroom broth to a simmer. Heat 2 tablespoons butter and the 1 remaining tablespoon oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the squash, onion, porcinis, and &frac12; teaspoon salt; cook, stirring, for 5 minutes. Add the rice and toast, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Add the wine and simmer, stirring, until absorbed, about 1 minute. Add 3 cups hot broth, return to simmer and cook, stirring, until most of the liquid is absorbed, 8 to 10 more minutes. Add 3 more cups broth and mushroom mixture; bring to a simmer and cook, stirring, until rice is ''al dente'', 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the remaining 1 tablespoon butter, the grated cheese and parsley.%0a%3c %0a%3c # Add more broth if needed, season with salt and garnish with the shaved cheese to serve.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comment%0a%3c Pair with FennelArugulaSalad for a great dinner, add ChocolateOliveOilFigCake for a sumptuous feast.%0a%3c %0a%3c Serve with a light to medium red wine, such as a Merlot, Beaujolais, Nebbilolo, or Valpolicella.%0a%3c %0a%3c >>comment%3c%3c%0a%3c Summary:a very tasty sounding Italian dish fit for a dinner party%0a%3c Parent:(Recipes.)MainDishes%0a%3c includeme:[[(Recipes.)MainDishes]]%0a%3c Source: Food Network Magazine, October 2012, Page 131%0a%3c Categories:[[!Recipes]],[[!MainDish]],[[!ItalianCuisine]]%0a%3c Tags: mushrooms, rice, risotto, shiitake, porcini, crimini%0a%3c (:tags-hide mushrooms, rice, risotto, shiitake, porcini, crimini:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a
